---
import DefaultLayout from "../layouts/DefaultLayout.astro";
---

<DefaultLayout>
  <div class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Research Areas</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 max-w-4xl">
      Our research spans multiple areas of radio astronomy, from theoretical
      modeling to observational studies and advanced data analysis techniques.
      We combine cutting-edge machine learning methods with world-class radio
      telescope observations to advance our understanding of transient radio
      phenomena.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Main Research Areas -->
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Primary Research Focus
    </h3>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      <!-- Fast Radio Bursts -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <div
            class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-blue-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4"
          >
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-600"
              fill="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 20 20"
            >
              <path
                d="M9.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.07 3.292a1 1 0 00.95.69h3.462c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-2.8 2.034a1 1 0 00-.364 1.118l1.07 3.292c.3.921-.755 1.688-1.54 1.118l-2.8-2.034a1 1 0 00-1.175 0l-2.8 2.034c-.784.57-1.838-.197-1.539-1.118l1.07-3.292a1 1 0 00-.364-1.118L2.98 8.72c-.783-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h3.461a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.07-3.292z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-gray-900">
              Fast Radio Bursts (FRBs)
            </h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              Investigation of Fast Radio Bursts through automated detection,
              classification, and morphological analysis. We develop machine
              learning pipelines for distinguishing genuine FRB signals from
              radio frequency interference and conduct observational studies
              using radio telescopes.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md">
              <h5 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Key Projects:</h5>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                <li>• Automated classification techniques for FRB detection</li>
                <li>
                  • Multi-frequency analysis across different radio wavelengths
                </li>
                <li>• Studies of repeating FRBs and their characteristics</li>
                <li>• Radio telescope observational campaigns</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Magnetars and Pulsars -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <div
            class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-purple-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4"
          >
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6 text-purple-600"
              fill="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 20 20"
            >
              <path
                fill-rule="evenodd"
                d="M11.3 1.046A1 1 0 0112 2v5h4a1 1 0 01.82 1.573l-7 10A1 1 0 018 18v-5H4a1 1 0 01-.82-1.573l7-10a1 1 0 011.12-.38z"
                clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-gray-900">
              Magnetars and Radio Transients
            </h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              Study of magnetars as FRB progenitors and their role in complex
              magneto-turbulent environments. Our work includes polarization
              studies of magnetars near the Galactic Center and observations
              with phased ALMA to explore radio transients in the mm/sub-mm
              window.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md">
              <h5 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Current Work:</h5>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                <li>
                  • Polarization studies of magnetars using ALMA observations
                </li>
                <li>• Radio pulsar research as analogs for FRB studies</li>
                <li>• Radio transient surveys across different frequencies</li>
                <li>
                  • Analysis of pulse characteristics and energy distributions
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Machine Learning and Data Science -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <div
            class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-green-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4"
          >
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6 text-green-600"
              fill="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 20 20"
            >
              <path
                d="M3 4a1 1 0 011-1h12a1 1 0 011 1v2a1 1 0 01-1 1H4a1 1 0 01-1-1V4zM3 10a1 1 0 011-1h6a1 1 0 011 1v6a1 1 0 01-1 1H4a1 1 0 01-1-1v-6zM14 9a1 1 0 00-1 1v6a1 1 0 001 1h2a1 1 0 001-1v-6a1 1 0 00-1-1h-2z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-gray-900">
              Machine Learning & Big Data Analytics
            </h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              Development of advanced algorithms for automated processing and
              predictive modeling of large astronomical datasets. Our expertise
              spans deep learning, statistical methods, and domain transfer
              techniques for cross-telescope applications.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md">
              <h5 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Techniques & Tools:
              </h5>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                <li>
                  • Deep neural networks for transient event classification
                </li>
                <li>
                  • Domain transfer learning for multi-telescope deployment
                </li>
                <li>• Unsupervised clustering for morphological analysis</li>
                <li>• Statistical methods and numerical simulations</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Astronomical Instrumentation -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <div
            class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 bg-orange-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mr-4"
          >
            <svg
              class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600"
              fill="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 20 20"
            >
              <path
                fill-rule="evenodd"
                d="M3 3a1 1 0 000 2v8a2 2 0 002 2h2.586l-1.293 1.293a1 1 0 101.414 1.414L10 15.414l2.293 2.293a1 1 0 001.414-1.414L12.414 15H15a2 2 0 002-2V5a1 1 0 100-2H3zm11.707 4.707a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L10 9.586 8.707 8.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z"
                clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-gray-900">
              Astronomical Instrumentation
            </h4>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              Research and development of radio astronomy instrumentation,
              including optimization of detection systems and advancement of
              observational techniques for transient source studies.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-md">
              <h5 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Instrumentation Work:
              </h5>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-1">
                <li>• Radio telescope observation optimization</li>
                <li>• Development of data processing methods</li>
                <li>• Multi-telescope observational techniques</li>
                <li>• High time resolution analysis methods</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Telescope Facilities -->
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Observatory Partnerships
    </h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div
        class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 rounded-lg p-6 border border-blue-200"
      >
        <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-blue-900">
          ALMA Observatory
        </h4>
        <p class="text-blue-800 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed">
          Radio observations at millimeter wavelengths using ALMA facilities.
          These observations enable studies of radio transients and magnetars in
          unique frequency regimes.
        </p>
        <div class="text-xs text-blue-700 space-y-1">
          <div>• High-frequency radio observations</div>
          <div>• Magnetar studies</div>
          <div>• Galactic Center research</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 rounded-lg p-6 border border-green-200"
      >
        <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-green-900">
          Radio Telescope Networks
        </h4>
        <p class="text-green-800 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed">
          Collaboration with various radio telescope facilities for FRB research
          and development of detection algorithms for multi-frequency
          observations.
        </p>
        <div class="text-xs text-green-700 space-y-1">
          <div>• Machine learning algorithm development</div>
          <div>• FRB detection research</div>
          <div>• Multi-frequency studies</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-violet-50 rounded-lg p-6 border border-purple-200"
      >
        <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-purple-900">
          Effelsberg L-band (1.3–1.8 GHz)
        </h4>
        <p class="text-purple-800 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed">
          Validation and expansion of DRAFTS pipelines through independent
          telescope observations. Cross-validation with FAST detections enables
          robust population studies and technique verification.
        </p>
        <div class="text-xs text-purple-700 space-y-1">
          <div>• DRAFTS pipeline validation</div>
          <div>• Cross-telescope comparison studies</div>
          <div>• FRB database expansion</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Methodology -->
  <section class="mb-12 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-8">
    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Research Methodology
    </h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div>
        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-900">
          Observational Approach
        </h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 text-sm">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span
              class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mt-2 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"
            ></span>
            Multi-frequency observations across L-band, mm-wave, and sub-mm wavelengths
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span
              class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mt-2 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"
            ></span>
            High time resolution studies with microsecond precision
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span
              class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mt-2 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"
            ></span>
            Polarization analysis and spectro-temporal characterization
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span
              class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full mt-2 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"
            ></span>
            Targeted follow-up observations of transient sources
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-900">
          Computational Methods
        </h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 text-sm">
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span
              class="w-2 h-2 bg-green-500 rounded-full mt-2 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"
            ></span>
            Deep learning architectures optimized for astronomical time series
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span
              class="w-2 h-2 bg-green-500 rounded-full mt-2 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"
            ></span>
            Statistical analysis of large-scale survey data
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span
              class="w-2 h-2 bg-green-500 rounded-full mt-2 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"
            ></span>
            Numerical simulations and predictive modeling
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start">
            <span
              class="w-2 h-2 bg-green-500 rounded-full mt-2 mr-3 flex-shrink-0"
            ></span>
            Cross-platform validation and domain adaptation
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Future Directions -->
  <section class="mb-12">
    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Future Research Directions
    </h3>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-900">
            Expanding Observational Horizons
          </h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed">
            Integration of next-generation radio facilities and development of
            real-time transient alert systems. Expansion to new frequency ranges
            and increased international collaboration for global FRB monitoring
            networks.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-900">
            Advanced Analytics
          </h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed">
            Development of more sophisticated machine learning models
            incorporating multi-messenger astronomy data. Enhanced real-time
            processing capabilities and automated discovery pipelines for rapid
            transient characterization.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DefaultLayout>
